│ I've identified the root cause of the dominance bug: the `setInsertPointAfterBundle` function uses a simplistic and incorrect heuristic for placing vectorized instructions. It places   │
│ the new instruction after the last scalar instruction in the bundle, which can be inside a loop and not dominate all uses, especially when operands come from outside the loop.          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The correct approach is to find an insertion point that dominates all the scalar instructions being vectorized. A safe and robust way to do this is to find the nearest common dominator │
│ basic block for all scalar instructions in the `TreeEntry` and place the new vectorized instruction at the beginning of that block (specifically, after any PHI nodes).                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will replace the current implementation of `setInsertPointAfterBundle` with one that computes the common dominator and sets the insertion point there. This will ensure that the       │
│ generated vector instructions are always placed in a location that dominates the original scalar instructions, thus preventing this class of dominance-related crashes.                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '13728,13745c\                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ void BoUpSLP::setInsertPointAfterBundle(const TreeEntry *E) {\                                                                                                                           │
│   BasicBlock *DomBB = nullptr;\                                                                                                                                                          │
│   if (E->getMainOp())\                                                                                                                                                                   │
│     DomBB = E->getMainOp()->getParent();\                                                                                                                                                │
│   for (Value *V : E->Scalars) {\                                                                                                                                                         │
│     if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {\                                                                                                                                           │
